<!-- STEP 3 -->
<section class="mb-32">

<h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-6">
Step 3 — Recommendation
</h2>

<p class="text-slate-600 max-w-4xl mb-10">
I recommended implementing a Power BI inventory allocation dashboard updated weekly via SQL.
The tool highlights surplus/shortage regions, demand drivers, and allows operations managers
to simulate redistribution scenarios before committing logistics resources.
</p>

<div class="bg-white p-10 rounded-3xl shadow">
<h3 class="font-bold mb-6">Inventory Reallocation Simulation</h3>

<label class="font-semibold">Demand uplift scenario (%)</label>
<input id="simSlider" type="range" min="0" max="30" value="10" class="w-full my-4"/>

<canvas id="simulationChart"></canvas>
</div>

</section>

<!-- STEP 4 -->
<section class="mb-32">

<h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-6">
Step 4 — Implementation
</h2>

<ul class="list-disc ml-6 text-slate-600 mb-10 max-w-4xl">
<li>Automated SQL ETL jobs refreshing weekly.</li>
<li>Power BI dashboard with slicers for region/month/vehicle class.</li>
<li>Operational alerting for shortages.</li>
<li>Scenario sliders for logistics planning.</li>
</ul>

<div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-8">

